column5: Remember your life before kids? And you thought you were busy? What a naive fool I was.  Anyway, boat is ready. Started first try in the driveway. I was sooooo tempted to make a quick run to the lake before picking up the kids. Maybe Wednesday afternoon.  Winter was too long.
missed a spot....looking good!!! I hope to get mine ready this weekend...the water on Dalrymple is so high you can`t even see where the launch is!!!
Looking good - now all she needs is forts slime of the season.
Looks great!!!,Good luck on your wednesday run!.I'm not long behind you.
Hmm,playing with yer Johnson I see.  Nice Rob.  Have a great season.
Looks great!  That's my next task as well....just need to be able to get to my boat in the garage!!!
yup. looks ready to  go  mine isn't ready to go but I have been out twice  it will be ready for simcoe opener
Needs some sliiime!  Looking good Rob.
Someone else is almost water ready.    Came home with the kids and had to spend 5 minutes explaining that just because the pool was in front of our house doesn't mean it's ours.

...yup that's how i remember her...started up like gold every spring for me too. Glad that you are having the same results! My new boat is still in storage and its killing me thinking about it. Hope this motor is as trusty as that one!
You can't have it back yet, but if/when I up-size I'll give you first crack.
haha...I was in some pretty hairy conditions on St. Clair last year...happy to be in the bigger, heavier boat I have now. But for Kawarthas? I would take that one back in a heartbeat
Ran around Kempenfelt Bay this afternoon. Might get out Saturday for trout if the storms hold off.
